TI  - Natural Language Processing in Electronic Health Records: Opportunities and Challenges
JO  - Journal of Biomedical Informatics
VL  - 128
SP  - 104567
PY  - 2023
DO  - 10.1016/j.jbi.2023.104567
AB  - Electronic health records contain vast amounts of unstructured text data that could provide valuable insights for clinical research and patient care. This review examines natural language processing techniques applied to EHR data, including named entity recognition, relation extraction, and clinical decision support systems.
